The government of Belize proposes an action plan to achieve the target reductions based on the following sub-components:
 
i.	Technical capacity development;
ii.	Recovery, reuse and recycling; 
iii.	Assistance for the use of hydrocarbon refrigerant equipment;
iv.	Refrigeration and air conditioning excellence centre and development of national expertise capacity;
v.	Synergy between energy efficiency and HCFC phase out in the tourism and hotel sector;
vi.	Improved Policy and Legal Framework to support HCFC Phase out; 
vii.	Capacity Building for Enhanced Control of Trade of HCFC-based Substances and Equipment, and
viii.	Monitoring, Evaluation and Reporting.
This project is being implemented as a joint UNDP/UNEP initiative. UNDP is directly responsible for Component 2; Recovery, Reuse and Recycle. The primary associated action is the purchasing of Equipment.
